# Task and chat summaries (recall)

## When to do it

- After a **substantive** task (multi-step fix, investigation, migration plan) or when the user asks for a **summary / memo / handoff**.
- Also when the user says **memorize**, **save for later**, or **recall**.

## Where to save

| Scope | Location |
|-------|----------|
| **EMCAP / this repo** | `docs/dev/session-memos/YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md` + one row in `docs/dev/recall-index.md` |
| **Other projects (default)** | `C:\Users\u1074139\.cursor\task-summaries\` — **never** inside unrelated git roots unless user explicitly requests a repo path |

## File naming

`YYYY-MM-DD-<short-slug>.md` (e.g. `2026-06-20-phase28-remediation-plan.md`).

## What to put in each file (compact, reusable)

1. **Goal / ticket** (if any)
2. **Decisions / constraints** (including no commit before review, user prefs)
3. **What changed** (paths, high level — not a full diff)
4. **Verification** (commands/tests run)
5. **Open follow-ups**

## In chat

- Tell the user **the full path** of the file you wrote so they can open or search it later.
- For EMCAP: prefer in-repo memos so they ship with the project and appear in `recall-index.md`.
